{
  "text": "To bound the term ramified P \u2208P 1 (Fq(t)/Fq ) w P (\u03c3) of (1), notice that it is enough to bound the number of places of degree 1 of F q (t) that ramify in M , as 0 \u2264 w P (\u03c3) \u2264 1. Notice that all places of F q (t) ramifying in M already ramify in F q (\u03b1), because M is the Galois closure of F q (\u03b1) : F q (t). Now apply Hurwitz genus formula (see [CITATION_1] Theorem 3.4.13] ) to see that there are at most 4 places of F q (t) that ramify in F q (\u03b1).",
